WORK SUMMARY :
The session began with an introduction to MVC (Model-View-Controller) Architecture. We learned that MVC is a design pattern used to separate an application
into three main components: Model, View, and Controller. The Model manages the data and business logic, the View is responsible for the user interface, and the
Controller acts as an intermediary between the Model and View. The trainer explained how this separation improves code organization, scalability, and maintainability
in web applications.

LEARNING OUTCOMES :
Understood the concept and structure of MVC Architecture
Learned the roles of Model, View, and Controller in application development
